This paper focuses on designing efficient algorithms for mining frequent itemsets, which is a common task in data mining and falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper specifically discusses the use of MapReduce framework, which is a distributed computing paradigm, and thus falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of data mining techniques and algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM).
